void curlyqueue_destroy_queue ( curlyqueue_t *  queue  ) 

Rolls through list, freeing resources.

Parameters:
queue the q to destroy
Precondition:
The queue pointer is not NULL
Postcondition:
All nodes in the list are freed

The list manager's pointers are set to null

The list manager's count is decremented for each freed node

void curlyqueue_enqueue ( curlyqueue_t *  queue,
void *  value 
)

Creates a node for a given value and adds it to the back of a queue.

Parameters:
queue The queue to add the value to
value The value to push onto the q
Postcondition:
The queue's count is incremented

Iterator is set to queue->back (to remove the need for remembering if the iter was initalized or not,ie to avoid the possibility of a null iter if there are items in list)
